&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;option 1. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To &lt;strong&gt;&amp;lsquo;pull someone&amp;rsquo;s leg&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;rsquo; means to make fun of them or laugh at them.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To &lt;strong&gt;&amp;lsquo;shoot fish in a barrel&amp;rsquo;&lt;/strong&gt; means to be do something that is mind-numbingly easy.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To &amp;lsquo;&lt;strong&gt;play hardball&amp;rsquo;&lt;/strong&gt; means to deal seriously, to act aggressively or in an unforgiving way.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To &lt;strong&gt;&amp;lsquo;put the cart before the horse&amp;rsquo;&lt;/strong&gt; means to reverse the normal order of something.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Thus, the correct option is &lt;strong&gt;1,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;since the context of the sentence suggests that even though Lawrence started crying, Jack was only trying to light-heartedly make fun of him.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Defame&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The most appropriate synonym of the given word &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Vilify&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Defame&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vilify&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;to say or write unpleasant things about somebody/something to make other people have a bad opinion of them. (अप्रिय बात लिखना या कहना; बदनाम करना; निंदा करना)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;Halle&amp;#39;s husband tried to &lt;strong&gt;vilify&lt;/strong&gt; her during their child custody battle.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Defame&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;to harm somebody by saying or writing bad or false things about him/her. (मानहानि करना, निंदा करना)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;The article is an &lt;strong&gt;attempt&lt;/strong&gt; to defame an honest man.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
		&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Answer:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Defame.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s look at the &lt;strong&gt;meaning &lt;/strong&gt;of other words:

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desert&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;to leave somebody/something, usually forever. [किसी को (प्रायः सदा के लिए) छोड़ जाना]&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deprive&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;to prevent somebody/something from having something; to take away something from somebody. (किसी को किसी से वंचित करना; किसी से कोई वस्&amp;zwj;तु छीन लेना)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deceive&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;to try to make somebody believe something that is not true. (बहकाना, भ्रमित करना)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The word &amp;lsquo;&lt;strong&gt;resolution&amp;rsquo;&lt;/strong&gt; means a firm decision to do or not to do something. Hence, &lt;strong&gt;option 2&lt;/strong&gt; ie. &lt;strong&gt;decision&lt;/strong&gt; must be its synonym.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are the meanings of the other options:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;list-style-type: disc;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;inclination&lt;/strong&gt; - an interest in or liking for (something)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;impressio&lt;/strong&gt;n - an idea, feeling, or opinion about something or someone&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;permission&lt;/strong&gt; - the action of officially allowing someone to do a something&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The correct answer is option 2.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Despise&lt;/strong&gt; means&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;feeling contempt or a deep repugnance. (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;अवमानना ​​या गहरी प्रतिद्वंद्विता महसूस करना।&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Approval &lt;/strong&gt;means&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;the action of approving something. (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;किसी चीज को मंजूरी देने की क्रिया&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Detest &lt;/strong&gt;means&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;dislike intensely. (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;तीव्र नापसंद&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;For eg; He really did detest his taste in food.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is clear that despise and detest are similar in meaning.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Respect &lt;/strong&gt;means&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;a feeling of deep admiration for someone or something elicited by their abilities, qualities, or achievements. (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;किसी व्यक्ति या किसी चीज़ के लिए उनकी क्षमताओं, गुणों या उपलब्धियों के लिए गहरी प्रशंसा की भावना&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Favor &lt;/strong&gt;means&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;approval, support, or liking for someone or something. (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;अनुमोदन, समर्थन, या किसी को या किसी चीज़ के लिए पसंद करना&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;So, options 1,3, and 4 are incorrect.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The word &amp;lsquo;&lt;strong&gt;pernicious&amp;rsquo;&lt;/strong&gt; means &amp;lsquo;having a harmful effect, especially in a gradual or subtle way&amp;rsquo;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Out of the given options, we can see that the word closest in meaning to this word is &amp;lsquo;&lt;strong&gt;spiteful&amp;rsquo;&lt;/strong&gt; which means &amp;lsquo;wanting to upset or hurt someone&amp;rsquo;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, &lt;strong&gt;option 2 is correct.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Calligraphy&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In the given context, the most appropriate one-word substitute for the group of words&lt;strong&gt; &amp;quot;the art of producing beautiful handwriting&amp;quot; is &amp;quot;Calligraphy&amp;quot; (option 3)&lt;/strong&gt;.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lexicography&lt;/strong&gt; - (लेक्सिकोग्राफी) The practice of compiling dictionaries or the study of the structure, usage, and meaning of words. &lt;em&gt;Example: She was fascinated by &lt;strong&gt;lexicography&lt;/strong&gt; and spent hours researching word origins.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Demography&lt;/strong&gt; - (जनसांख्यिकी) The statistical study of populations, especially human populations, including their size, structure, and distribution. &lt;em&gt;Example: The &lt;strong&gt;demography&lt;/strong&gt; of the city showed a significant increase in the younger population.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calligraphy&lt;/strong&gt; - (कैलीग्राफी) The art of producing decorative handwriting or lettering with a pen or brush. &lt;em&gt;Example: She practiced &lt;strong&gt;calligraphy&lt;/strong&gt; diligently to create stunning wedding invitations.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Graphology&lt;/strong&gt; - (ग्राफोलॉजी) The pseudoscientific study of handwriting, often claimed to reveal personality traits or psychological characteristics. &lt;em&gt;Example: Some employers use &lt;strong&gt;graphology&lt;/strong&gt; to analyze job applicants&amp;#39; handwriting.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Defiant&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Antonym means &lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;a&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;phrase or word with the opposite meaning as another phrase or word.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;Flexible&lt;/strong&gt; means that can be changed easily or that agrees with anything.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;Defiant&lt;/strong&gt; means openly refusing to obey something or somebody.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;em&gt;meaning of word flexible is opposite of the meaning of word Defiant&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, &lt;strong&gt;option 2 i.e. Defiant&lt;/strong&gt; is the answer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;compliant&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;refers &lt;strong&gt;to a person or thing that is willing to follow rules or orders, or conform to a standard or regulation.&lt;/strong&gt; It can also mean that someone is agreeable or submissive in nature.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Example: &amp;quot;The company&amp;#39;s products are &lt;strong&gt;compliant &lt;/strong&gt;with all relevant safety regulations.&amp;quot;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;Peculiar&lt;/strong&gt; means unusual or strange.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Example : I was in a very &lt;strong&gt;peculiar &lt;/strong&gt;situation today.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;Reckless&lt;/strong&gt; means&amp;nbsp;not considering the negative or dangerous consequences of your actions
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Example : He is the most &lt;strong&gt;reckless &lt;/strong&gt;person I have ever met.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The word &amp;lsquo;&lt;strong&gt;treachery&amp;rsquo;&lt;/strong&gt; means &amp;lsquo;betrayal of trust&amp;rsquo;. This is clearly opposite in meaning to the word &amp;lsquo;&lt;strong&gt;fidelity&amp;rsquo;&lt;/strong&gt; which means &amp;lsquo;faithfulness or loyalty&amp;rsquo;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Devotion &lt;/strong&gt;means&amp;nbsp;love, loyalty, or enthusiasm for a person or activity.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Fierceness &lt;/strong&gt;means the quality of being fierce ie. bold.&lt;/p&gt;
Hence, &lt;strong&gt;option 3 is correct.&lt;/strong&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;dusk&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dusk&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;is the transition from day to night.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Example- The park closes at&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;dusk.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given phrase appropriately describes&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;dusk&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;So it is the most appropriate option.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dawn&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;is the first appearance of light in the sky.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Example- He set off for Delhi at &lt;strong&gt;dawn&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;b&gt;Option 4&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The idiom &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Go down like a lead balloon&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means to be received badly by an audience. (दर्शकों द्वारा बुरी तरह से स्वीकार किया जाना)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; His joke during the presentation &lt;strong&gt;went down like a lead balloon.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To be received badly by an audience&lt;/strong&gt; refers to a situation where something, such as a performance or a joke, fails to impress or entertain the audience. (दर्शकों द्वारा बुरी तरह से स्वीकार किया जाना)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The new product launch&lt;strong&gt; went down like a lead balloon&lt;/strong&gt; with the customers.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;Option 4&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meanings and example sentences:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Put yourself in a tough position in order to support someone / something&lt;/strong&gt; (किसी का / किसी चीज़ का समर्थन करने के लिए अपने आप को कठिन स्थिति में डालना):

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; He put himself in a tough position to support his friend during the crisis.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Surrender&lt;/strong&gt; (आत्मसमर्पण करना):
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The soldiers had to surrender after running out of ammunition.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To gamble everything you have&lt;/strong&gt; (जो कुछ भी आपके पास है, उस पर जुआ खेलना):
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; He decided to gamble everything he had on that risky investment.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;option&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;3. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/20/09/428%20%281%29.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 48px; height: 48px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Explanation:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;To &amp;lsquo;hit the sack&amp;rsquo; means to go to bed.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;To &amp;lsquo;make a long story short&amp;rsquo; means to cut to the end of a story and make it short.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;To &amp;lsquo;g&lt;strong&gt;et the ball rolling&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;rsquo; means to set an activity in motion, to make a start.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;To &amp;lsquo;let someone off the hook&amp;rsquo; means to let someone go easily, without punishment or consequence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thus, the correct answer is option &lt;strong&gt;3.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;option 4)To achieve two things by doing a single action&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The idiom &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;kill two birds with one stone&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; is a figurative expression that means&lt;strong&gt; to accomplish two objectives with a single action&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It implies efficiency and productivity by solving two problems at once or accomplishing two goals with a single effort.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The phrase originates from the practice of hunting, where a stone is thrown to hit and kill a bird, and it is an efficient way to catch two birds with one throw.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The word &amp;lsquo;&lt;strong&gt;ambidextrous&amp;rsquo;&lt;/strong&gt; means &amp;lsquo;able to use the right and left hands equally well&amp;rsquo;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, &lt;strong&gt;option 4 is correct.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are the meanings of the other words:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;list-style-type: disc;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ambiguous&lt;/strong&gt; - open to more than one interpretation&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ambivalent&lt;/strong&gt; - having mixed feelings about something&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Amiable&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; pleasant and friendly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Infallible&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The most appropriate word for the given group of words is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Infallible&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It means &amp;#39;(used about a person) never making mistakes or being wrong&amp;#39;. [(व्&amp;zwj;यक्ति) जो कभी भूलें न करें या ग़लती पर न हो; अमोघ]
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;No computer is &lt;strong&gt;infallible&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s look at the meaning of other words:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pure&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;not mixed with anything else. [शुद्घ (बिना मिलावट का)]&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Optimist&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;a person who tends to be hopeful and confident about the future or the success of something. (आशावादी व्यक्ति)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Naive&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;without enough experience of life and too ready to believe or trust other people. (जिसे जीवन का पर्याप्त अनुभव नहीं और जो दूसरों पर तुरंत विश्&amp;zwj;वास या भरोसा कर लेता है; भोला-भाला)&lt;br /&gt;
		&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Answer:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Infallible.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Finish.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Initiate:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;to cause something to begin&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Finish:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;bring (a task or activity) to an end; complete&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thus, we can see that &lt;u&gt;Initiate&lt;/u&gt; and &lt;u&gt;Finish&lt;/u&gt; are antonyms.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The meaning of the other words:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Start:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;to begin doing something&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Begin:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;to start to do something&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Commence:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;to begin something especially a shop or business.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Initiate&lt;/strong&gt;: to take first step in doing something especially something new.&lt;br /&gt;
	&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Start, Begin, Commence&amp;nbsp;and Initiate&amp;nbsp;are all near-synonyms.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

